Package model.decoration.table.element

Package containing all implementations of Elements needed for the Decoration Table.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Affectation
    Implementation of an Affection An Affectation is an Element It's also an affectation of an Element in a Variable
    Division
    Implentation of a product between two Element
    Element
    Superclass Element Base for every values/functions/Variables/Instruction needed in the whole model With this superclass we can easily nest elements in each other and create logic instructions.
    Function
    Implementation of a function A Function is an Element Is described by its name and a List of parameters
    IndexedVariable
    Implementation of an indexed Variable An IndexedVariable is also a Variable and obviously an Element An IndexedVariable is described by its name and a value representing the distance from the relative index
    IntegerVal
    Implementation of an integer as an Element Basically just an Integer, but also an Element
    Operation
    Implentation of an operation between two Element
    Product
    Implentation of a product between two Element
    Substraction
    Implentation of a soustraction between two Element
    Sum
    Implentation of a sum between two Element
    Variable
    Implementation of a Variable as Element Identified by a name
